        "city_summary": "Hershey is an unincorporated community and census-designated place (CDP) in Derry Township, Dauphin County, Pennsylvania, United States. It is home to the Hershey Company, which was founded by candy magnate Milton S. Hershey, and Hersheypark, an amusement park.\nThe community is located 14 miles (23 km) east of Harrisburg and is part of the Harrisburg metropolitan area.",
